'''Alexandria''' ({{IPA-ro|aleˈksandri.a|-|Ro-Alexandria.ogg}}) is the capital city of the [[Teleorman County]], [[Romania]]. It is located south-west of [[Bucharest]], towards the Bulgarian border. The city is situated on the [[Vedea River]] and has over 45,000 inhabitants.
{{Historical populations |source = Census data |1912 |15785 |1930 |19350 |1948 |17840 |1956 |19294 |1966 |21898 |1977 |37340 |1992 |58478 |2002 |50591 |2011 |45434 }}
==Early history== Alexandria was named after its founder, '''[[Alexandru II Ghica|Alexandru D. Ghica]]''', [[List of rulers of Wallachia|Prince]] of [[Wallachia]] from April 1834 to 7 October 1842. Its population in 1900 was 1,675. Its chief trade then, was in grain, dispatched by rail to the Danubian port of [[Zimnicea]], or by river to [[Giurgiu]].<ref name="EB1911">{{EB1911|inline=y|wstitle=Alexandria (Rumania)|display=Alexandria|volume=1|page=572}}</ref>
==Alexandria before the 1989 Revolution== In 1989, the city had over 63,000 inhabitants and more than six large factories.
